profile_positions.description:
Sewage Collection and Treatment and Solid Waste Disposal Program
 (Environmental compensation project for the rupture of a mining tailings dam in Mariana, Brazil, occurred in 2015).
Main activities: 
•	Support in program structuring (creation of processes and identification of activities of different stakeholders, project submission flow and transfer of resources, etc.);
•	Direct management support;
•	Elaboration of technical reports;
•	Product and service purchases (preparation of technical requisition, quantity and price table, proposal evaluation);
•	Supervision of technical support team to municipalities, for implementation of sewage collection and treatment systems and adequate disposal of solid waste.

State Environmental Foundation of Minas Gerais, Brazil / Effluent Monitoring Management (Minas Treat Sewage Program).
Main activities: 
•	Collection and analysis of data and information from sewage collection and treatment systems;
•	Diagnosis and prognosis of basic sanitation situation of municipalities of Minas Gerais state;
•	Collection and analysis of data from the environmental monitoring process of industrial effluents;
•	Diagnosis of environmental impacts about the river Das Velhas basin, Belo Horizonte, Brazil.

Update and Modernization of the National Portal of Environmental Licensing

Main activities: 
•	Distribution and monitoring of activities; 
•	Meeting with state environmental agencies; 
•	Collection and analysis of data about modality and stages of licensing; procedures for license request, consent of intervening agencies; types of environmental studies requested, license evaluation and approval criterions;
•	Diagnostic and macroprocesses elaboration of the procedures for environmental licensing of enterprises and activities in the states.
